column17:
## Primary Diagnosis (by "Side + Joint Name + Injury Structure + Injury Type")
**Degenerative cartilage/joint space degeneration injury of the right hip (femoral head-acetabular joint) (osteoarthritis, severe)**

---

## Basis for diagnosis

### 1) Characteristics of medical history
- **Discomfort in the right hip for 5 years**, gradually worsening, with **limited mobility**;
- Currently able to walk but **lame**, unable to run, climb, ball games and other weight-bearing/impact sports - in line with the characteristics of **hip degenerative disease** chronic progression and functional limitation.

### 2) Physical examination
- Right hip **no significant redness** (does not support acute suppuration/acute inflammatory arthritis);
- Right hip**limited movement in all directions of flexion, extension, and rotation** - in line with the common "omnidirectional limited movement (especially rotation limitation)" manifestations of hip osteoarthritis;
- No signs of neurovascular damage.

### 3) Key points of imaging (orthopelvic X-ray).
- **Noticeable narrowing/near disappearance of the right hip space** (suggesting severe wear and tear of the articular cartilage);
- **Osteophytes formation of the right femoral head and acetabulum margin**, irregular articular surfaces;
- Visible **subchondrosclerosis / cystic alteration** tendency;
- The left hip is relatively preserved, and the contrast is more supportive of the right hip as the main lesion side.

> The above X-ray combination signs (narrowing of the joint space + osteophytes + subchondrosclerosis/cystic degeneration) are typical imaging manifestations of **hip osteoarthritis (degenerative joint disease)**, and the degree is severe.

---

If you need to further differentiate it from "ankylosing spondylitis-related hip joint lesions", it is recommended to supplement: sacroiliac joint X-ray/CT or MRI, inflammatory indicators, HLA-B27, etc.; However, based on the hip X-rays and clinical manifestations currently available, the primary diagnosis is more consistent with severe degenerative osteoarthritis of the right hip.

